The SAPS Grahamstown task team recently conducted an intelligence led operation and arrested man for possession of dagga and plantation of dagga in Fingo Village, according to police spokesperson Captain Mali Govender. &ldquo;Police recovered 19 bompies in a brown envelope, weight 0.624kg; 41 bompies in a small envelope, weight 0.510kg; 10 plastic bompies, weight 0.168kg; three plastic bags of dagga, weight 0.244kg and five plants of dagga,&rdquo; Govender said. The suspect is due to appear in the Grahamstown Magistrate&rsquo;s Court soon.